      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You should absolutely not increase your controller inhaler dose without professional guidance. Controller medications are dosed precisely to manage chronic inflammation, and overdoing them can lead to side effects or build resistance. Instead of changing your prescription, focus on optimizing your technique and ensuring you are using it exactly as prescribed. If you feel the current dose isn't working, the only safe way to adjust it is through a consultation.",
      "source": "target",
